				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There are two independent address and data buses on an NES. Variables go at $0000 on the CPU bus; CHR goes at $0000 on the PPU bus.
<br />
<br />In NESASM, the .org you pass to your assembler determines only the address. The .bank partly determines which bus; the iNES format places CHR immediately after PRG.
<br />
<br />"Zelda" doesn't have a CHR ROM unless you're talking about The Adventure of Link. Instead, The Legend of Zelda has CHR RAM, where the CPU copies data from PRG ROM to RAM on the cartridge through a register on the PPU.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

